properties.Name: InsuranceProgram
properties.Description:
A specific program that may be applied to an insurance product or policy that results in a discount or favorable treatment.

Ex:
- Low Income Education Loan Program
- Senior Citizenship Program
- Student Shopped Program
- a product specific promotion program
- a program to educate the public or consumers about a product or service
- a support program such as 'product maintenance'

Note:
A Program may also be associated with an Order in which case it identifies the specific Program under which the associated Order was placed or fulfilled.

Boat Ex:
- US Coast Guard Safe Boating Program
- Power Squadron Safe Boating Program

Condominium Ex:
- Community Watch
- Employee of ... Discount
- Group discount program ("Members of...")

Earthquake Ex:
- California Earthquake Authority Condominium Coverage
- California Earthquake Authority Homeowners Coverage
- California Earthquake Authority Mobile home Coverage
- California Earthquake Authority Renters Coverage

Flood Ex:
National Flood Insurance Program (NFIP)
In 1968, Congress created the National Flood Insurance Program (NFIP) to help provide a means for property owners to financially protect themselves. The NFIP offers flood insurance to homeowners, renters, and business owners if their community participates in the NFIP. Participating communities agree to adopt and enforce ordinances that meet or exceed FEMA requirements to reduce the risk of flooding.

Homeowners' Ex:
- Community Watch
- Employee of ... Discount
- Group discount program ("Members of...")

Motorcycle Ex:
- Accident Forgiveness
- Military Safety course
- Motorcycle Safety Foundation course

Personal Umbrella Liability Ex:
- Member of organization

AFLAC association discount program available for chamber members not already participating in an established AFLAC individual or corporate policy.  Contact the chamber for a participating agent in our community

Recreational Vehicle (RV) Ex:
- AARP Program

Where:

AARP PROGRAM
The AARP Program from The Hartford offers specialized protection for the two main categories of RVs: Motor Homes (including van campers and conversion vehicles) and Towables, which include fifth wheel travel trailers, folding camping trailers, conventional travel trailers and truck campers.

Vehicle Ex:
- Driver Education
- Driver Improvement Course
- Driver Training

Where: 

DRIVER EDUCATION
State accredited educational course that consist of at least 30 hours of professional classroom instruction.

DRIVER IMPROVEMENT COURSE
A voluntary refresher course available for drivers age fifty-five (55) and older to enhance their driving skills.

DRIVER TRAINING
State accredited training course that consists of time spent behind-the-wheel with professional instruction.

Columns.Description: A statement of the restrictions that apply to access to or participation in the Program.

Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Program Type.

Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Product Type.

Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.
